race.comment: KING OF GERALDINE (7) missed the start then did a good job to finish just 1.5 lengths from the winner over 800m at Ipswich last start. Very fit after three runs back from a spell and is far better placed out to this trip. Looks hard to toss in an open race. SEAMS LOGICAL (5) opened his career with a couple of nice efforts at Warwick then wasn't disgraced in a good quality three-year-old race in town last time out. Beautifully drawn and poses a serious threat back in this company. SPIRITOFTHEWORLD (9) had a five-week let-up before breaking through over 1050m here last Saturday. Continues to improve and is capable of matching it against better opposition this evening. WANTED HILLBILLY (3) has struggled in two stronger races since a tough win over 1100m at Warwick on 11 October. In the right race to bounce back to form. Market watch on PROFITS PRAYER (10) resuming for the Currie stable.
